Body:
We have a libelium smart city kit, with which we have configured ambient sensor module and are able to connect the sensors (Waspmote) to the gateway (Meshlium) Meshlium is able receive the data from the sensors.

We have followed the recipes for Libelium: https://developer.ibm.com/recipes/tutorials/bluemix-configuration-guide-for-meshlium/

We set-up the API keys in bluemix and configured meshlium to connect bluemix
column9:
but blumix is not receiving the data yet.

We are also able to ping to Bluemix from meshlium.

Need some help on where we are going wrong and is there any additional set-up required both at Bluemix end and meshlium end.

"

Body: We did no coding. As per my post, which has the url for the recipe there was no requirement to do the coding. Are we missing anything here
Is the synchronization started on your device? What does the Bluemix dashboard show regarding your device?
Yes syn started. How to upload images? I can share you the screen captures
Were you able to check the logs? Any update please?
If you don't add your code, we won't be able to tell where you are going wrong.

Found an alternate route,  i.e.  Libellium has a plugin :MQTT Solutions. Using this plugin I can push the sensor data to a MQTT broker. We have created an IoTF service on ibm bluemix and have added this broker as the recipient of the data. We get connection time out. Can you help us to troubleshoot this issue?
Can you provide your unique 6 character org so we can check logs to see if it shows any errors for your connections?

@SabrishSurender  sorry for the delayed reply.  Are you still having the problem?  Looking in the logs today I see valid connections for your org.  Please tag me with @ sign if you reply so I will get a notification.
